A. CREATE :   
-----------
1.	Clone an existing repository  - git clone ssh://user@domin.com/repo.git
2.	Create a new local Repository - git init

B. LOCAL CHANGES :   
------------------
1.	Check Changed files in directory - git status
2.	Check Changes to track files     - git diff
3.  Add Changes to next Commit		 - git add .
4.  Add some changes <file> in commit- git add -p <file>
5.	Commit all local changes         - git commit -a "Comment"
6.  Change Last commit               - git commit --amend

C. COMMIT HISTORY :   
-------------------
1.	Show all commits start with newest - git log
2.  Show changes over time for a file  - git log -p <file>
3.	Who Changed What & When            - git blame  <file>

D. BRANCHES & TAGS :   
--------------------
1.  List all existing branches  - git branch -av
2.  Switch HEAD BRANCHES        - git checkout <branch>
3.	Create a new branch         - git branch <new-branch-name>
4.  Delete a local branch.      - git branch -d <branch>
5.  Mark the current commit     - git tag <tag Name>

E. UPDATE & PUBLISH :   
--------------------
1. List all currently configured remotes - git remote -v
2. Show information about a Remote       - git remote show <remote>
3. Add remote repository                 - git remote add <shortname> <url>
4. Dnld all chngs frm remote but intgrte - git fetch <remote>
5. Dnld changes & Dirctly merge into Head- git pull <remote> <branch>
6. Publish Local changes on a remote     - git push <remote> <branch>
7. Delete a branch on the remote         - git branch -dr <remote/branch>
8. publish your tags                     - git push --tags


F. MERGE & REBASE :   
-------------------
1.	Merge branch into current head               -  git merge <branch>


G. UNDO:   
--------
1.  Discard all local changes inyour working dir - git reset --hard HEAD
2.  Discard local changes in a specific file     - git checkout HEAD <FileName>
3.  Revert a commit                              - git revert <commit>
4.  Reset your HEAD Pointer to a previous commit - git reset -- hard <commit>
5.  Preserve all changes as unstaged changes     - git reset <commit>
6.  Preserve uncommited local changes            - git reset --keep <commit>




























